<li>It wouldn't be Halloween without something spooky. Luckily, <a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=94453">noeeel</a> is here to scratch that itch with <a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=59713129">a containment breach in progress...</a></li>
<li>Everybody's favorite <a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=3551005">dansen</a> is at it again with some more <a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=59636265">2521 fanart</a>!</li>
<li>This piece by <a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member.php?id=16783692">時果</a> depicts <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7061118); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=7061118&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437324" alt="Roget" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=7061118)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/roget" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(7061118); return false;">Roget</a></span>'s <a href="/scp-031">SCP-031</a> looking for love <a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?mode=medium&amp;illust_id=59620345">in all the wrong places...</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.pixiv.net/member_illust.php?id=13207113">mitasa's</a> got plenty of moe-SCPs to peek at, from 173 to 2999!</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p>Thanks for tuning in again, folks! If you're unsatisfied with the blurb(s) provided for the article(s) you wrote, feel free to change it. Of course, if you write an article and it sticks, <em>please</em> send <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437324" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span> or <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=209204&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1608437324" alt="rumetzen" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=209204)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rumetzen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(209204); return false;">rumetzen</a></span> a blurb for your article. We may or may not use it (if we can think of something more attention-getting, though we can try to stick with one you give us) but we'd really would just like them in order to make the process easier for making these. This is a community thing, and I want authors to give their blurbs to sell these articles much easier. It reduces the workload we have to do, and helps the news come out that much earlier!</p>
<p>Thank you all for continuing to be an excellent community &lt;3</p>
